               <p>THOMAS MEECHAM. I <rs id="t18270531-265-viclabel1432" type="occupation">keep the Duke of Cumberland public-house, Red Lion-street, Spitalfields</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-265-victim1462 t18270531-265-viclabel1432"></join>; the prisoner was brought in on the 10th of May, with a pint pot under his coat; I fetched a constable, who found two quart pots on him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-265-person1463">
                  JOHN 
                  FITZGERALD
               <interp inst="t18270531-265-person1463" type="surname" value="FITZGERALD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-265-person1463" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-265-person1463" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 10th of May I was at my house, No. 3, Red Lion-street; I saw the prisoner go up the steps of No. 2, and take some pots from the window cill; he had sweep's clothes on; I secured him, and took him to Meecham's; he said he was going to take them to the public-house, but he was going the wrong way - he dropped one.</p>
